trans-unit.source: Describes encryption and signature requirements that apply to different parts of messages that are transmitted on this channel.
trans-unit.target: Beskriver kryptering og krav til signatur som gjelder for forskjellige deler av meldinger som sendes på denne kanalen.

trans-unit.source: When extending the <xref:System.ServiceModel.Channels.BindingElement> class, you must implement the <xref:System.ServiceModel.Channels.BindingElement.GetProperty%60%601%28System.ServiceModel.Channels.BindingContext%29> so that it returns an instance of this class corresponding to the binding element.
trans-unit.target: Når du utvider den <xref:System.ServiceModel.Channels.BindingElement>klasse, må du implementere den <xref:System.ServiceModel.Channels.BindingElement.GetProperty%60%601%28System.ServiceModel.Channels.BindingContext%29>slik at det returnerer en forekomst av denne klassen som tilsvarer bindingselementet.</xref:System.ServiceModel.Channels.BindingElement.GetProperty%60%601%28System.ServiceModel.Channels.BindingContext%29> </xref:System.ServiceModel.Channels.BindingElement>

trans-unit.source: This default constructor sets the following properties to a new instance of <xref:System.ServiceModel.Security.ScopedMessagePartSpecification>, which is a class that specifies which parts are included in a message: - <xref:System.ServiceModel.Security.ChannelProtectionRequirements.IncomingEncryptionParts%2A>, - <xref:System.ServiceModel.Security.ChannelProtectionRequirements.IncomingSignatureParts%2A>, - <xref:System.ServiceModel.Security.ChannelProtectionRequirements.OutgoingEncryptionParts%2A>, and - <xref:System.ServiceModel.Security.ChannelProtectionRequirements.OutgoingSignatureParts%2A>.
trans-unit.target: Denne standardkonstruktør angir de følgende egenskapene til en ny forekomst av <xref:System.ServiceModel.Security.ScopedMessagePartSpecification>, som er en klasse som angir hvilke deler er inkludert i en melding:- <xref:System.ServiceModel.Security.ChannelProtectionRequirements.IncomingEncryptionParts%2A>, - <xref:System.ServiceModel.Security.ChannelProtectionRequirements.IncomingSignatureParts%2A>, - <xref:System.ServiceModel.Security.ChannelProtectionRequirements.OutgoingEncryptionParts%2A>, og - <xref:System.ServiceModel.Security.ChannelProtectionRequirements.OutgoingSignatureParts%2A>.</xref:System.ServiceModel.Security.ChannelProtectionRequirements.OutgoingSignatureParts%2A> </xref:System.ServiceModel.Security.ChannelProtectionRequirements.OutgoingEncryptionParts%2A> </xref:System.ServiceModel.Security.ChannelProtectionRequirements.IncomingSignatureParts%2A> </xref:System.ServiceModel.Security.ChannelProtectionRequirements.IncomingEncryptionParts%2A> </xref:System.ServiceModel.Security.ScopedMessagePartSpecification>

trans-unit.source: This constructor sets the following properties to a new instance of <xref:System.ServiceModel.Security.ScopedMessagePartSpecification>, using the <xref:System.ServiceModel.Security.ScopedMessagePartSpecification.%23ctor%2A> constructor, with `other` as the input parameter.
